{"action": "write_file", "file_content": "# CSS Vertical Theme Overrides

The paragu-ai-builder uses CSS custom properties for theming. The global `:root` defines defaults (blue primary, amber accent). Individual vertical landing pages can override the entire palette with a CSS class on the page's root `<div>`.

## Pattern

```css
/* In globals.css — ONE class overrides ALL CSS variables for a vertical */

.hair-theme {
  --primary: #c7765e;           /* rose/terracotta */
  --primary-foreground: #ffffff;
  --secondary: #a05a4a;
  --accent: #d4a373;            /* gold */
  --background: #fdf8f5;        /* warm cream */
  --foreground: #2c1810;        /* dark brown */
  --surface: #ffffff;
  --surface-light: #fef3ed;
  --muted-foreground: #7a5c4a;
  --border: #ecd9cf;            /* rose border */
  --shadow-card: 0 2px 8px rgba(199, 118, 94, 0.08);
  --shadow-card-hover: 0 8px 24px rgba(199, 118, 94, 0.15);
  --gradient-primary-accent: linear-gradient(135deg, #c7765e 0%, #d4a373 100%);
}

.barber-theme {
  --primary: #8b4513;           /* saddle brown */
  --secondary: #654321;
  --accent: #c4a265;            /* dark gold */
  --background: #f8f5f0;
  --foreground: #1a1410;
  --surface-light: #f5f0eb;
  --border: #d4c5b5;
}
```

## Usage in a page

```tsx
// app/peluqueria/page.tsx
export default function PeluqueriaPage() {
  return (
    <div className="hair-theme w-full">
      <SiteNav />
      <main>...content...</main>
      <SiteFooter />
    </div>
  )
}
```

## When to Create a New Theme

- Every new vertical landing page (`/peluqueria`, `/barberia`, `/spa`, `/veterinaria`) should get its own theme class
- Keep themes in `globals.css` grouped under a `/* VERTICAL THEMES */` section comment
- Override ALL variables that affect the page's feel: primary/accent colors, backgrounds, borders, shadows, gradients
- Do NOT override things like radius, spacing, transitions — those stay universal

## Palette Guidelines by Vertical

| Vertical | Vibe | Primary | Accent | Background |
|----------|------|---------|--------|------------|
| Hair salon (peluqueria) | Warm, rose, gold | `#c7765e` | `#d4a373` | `#fdf8f5` |
| Barberia | Dark, masculine, rich | `#8b4513` | `#c4a265` | `#f8f5f0` |
| Spa/Relaxation | Green, natural | (future) | (future) | (future) |
| Veterinary | Sky blue, clean | (future) | (future) | (future) |

## Notes

- The class must be on the OUTERMOST wrapper inside the page component (wraps everything including SiteNav and SiteFooter)
- CSS variable classes cascade through the entire subtree — no per-component styling needed
- All components use `var(--primary)`, `var(--background)`, etc. — they pick up the override automatically
